The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Bopanna off to a good start

New Delhi: Rohan Bopanna lived up to his billing as top seed scoring a facile 6-2, 6-2 victory over Tushar Liberhan in the first round of the State Bank of Saurashtra National Grasscourt Championships on Tuesday. 

Bopannas match completed first-round action in mens singles. On Monday, the likes of Karan Rastogi, Vijay Kannan and Vishal Uppal easily won their respective opening matches. The only flutter was caused by young Sanam Singh who eliminated the experienced Kamala Kannan. 

In doubles action on Day II, veteran Sandeep Kirtane and Purav Raja upset second seeds Kamala Kannan and V.S. Prasanth 7-6 (7-1), 6-2. 

Wild cards Jeevan Nedunchezhiyan and Sanam advanced with a 6-2, 6-4 verdict over Wrik Ganguly and Divyanshu Singh. 

In womens doubles, third seeds Geeta Manohar and Archana Venkataraman overcame Anupama and Chirashanthi Rajurs 6-3 7-6 (7-2). Second seeds Sanaa Bhambri and Sandhya Nagaraj blanked Asha Nandakumar and Oormila Ram 6-0, 6-0. 

Top seeds Rushmi Chakravarthi and Punam Reddy had a bye. 

 (PTI) 




